1. Job Board Application
Description: Build a platform where employers can post job listings and job seekers can create profiles, upload resumes, apply for jobs, and track applications. Include features like advanced search filters (location, job type, experience level), user authentication, and real-time notifications.

Technologies:
Front-end: React for a dynamic, responsive UI.

Back-end: Node.js with Express for handling job listings and user data.

Database: MongoDB for storing job postings and user profiles.

Other: Elasticsearch for search functionality, LinkedIn API for profile integration, WebSocket for real-time notifications.

Why Itâ€™s Valuable: Job boards are complex systems that demonstrate your ability to handle user authentication, database management, and scalable search functionality. The project aligns with real-world platforms like Indeed or LinkedIn, showing practical skills that employers seek. It also allows you to showcase UI/UX design and secure data handling.

Job Appeal: Companies value developers who can build user-centric, secure systems. This project highlights full-stack expertise and problem-solving, making it a strong talking point in interviews.

